#: 21337012-0-772
msgctxt "21337012-0-772"
msgid "Finally, the answer! In my dream, I saw the one whose strength will help me complete my quest to bring Falinesti back! Soon, very soon. Perhaps it will be Sundas again."
"\n"
"\nSundas. Does the year matter? The month? We first met on a Sundas. And on a Sundas many years later, he disappeared."
"\n"
"\nI took the pilgrimage to the other Falinesti Sites with the faithful. But I remembered we met on a Sundas at the Summer Site, and realized when the Walking City returns, it will be to the valley."
"\n"
"\nAnd of course, I'm right. The cracks between the Summer Site and Oblivion demonstrate how close the city is. Some nights, I can see its lights shimmering through the portals that flare into existence now and then."
"\n"
"\nWe'll be together soon, and the many, many years apart will mean nothing. It will be as it was that Sundas, when I first put my hand into his."
msgstr ""
"드디어 답을 찾았다! 꿈 속에서 내 탐구를 도와 팔리네스티를 다시 되돌릴 힘을 가진 사람을 목격했다! 금방, 아주 금방 만나게 될 것이다."
" 어쩌면 다음 선다스가 될지도 모르겠다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"선다스라. 몇 년도였더라? 무슨 달이었지? 우린 선다스에 처음 만났었지. 그리고 많은 시간이 흐른 뒤의 선다스에, 그이는 사라졌다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"신앙인들과 함께 다른 팔리네스티 땅에 순례도 다녀와봤다. 하지만 나는 우리가 선다스에 여름 땅에서 만났다는 것을 기억해냈고, 걸어다니는 "
"도시가 돌아오는 날에는 도시가 그 골짜기에 나타날 것이라는 사실을 깨달았다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"그리고 당연하게도 내 생각이 맞았다. 여름 땅과 오블리비언 사이에 난 틈은 도시가 얼마나 가까이에 있는지 보여주는 증거다. 이따금 밤이면 "
"포탈 사이로 도시의 존재를 보여주는 불빛이 타오르는 모습을 볼 수도 있다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"우리는 곧 다시 만날 것이다. 아주아주 오랜 세월동안 떨어져 있었다는 것도 아무런 의미가 없을 것이다. 내가 그이의 손을 처음으로 잡았던 "
"그날의 선다스처럼 될 것이다."

#: 51188213-0-772
msgctxt "51188213-0-772"
msgid "Farandare's Journal"
msgstr "파란다레의 일지"

#: 21337012-0-760
msgctxt "21337012-0-760"
msgid "I can't help but feel that My Lord Maurice is interested in me for more than my duties as a servant. He glanced at me several times these past weeks as I brought dinner to the table or poured the wine. He just smiles and looks into my eyes. Like I'm an equal. Not as if I were a young woman merely there to refill his flagon or clear away the dirty dishes, but as someone he might actually be interested in. I don't know what to think of it. I'm probably just imagining it, dreaming about what life would be like if I didn't have to serve and clean every day. It's a dream, but I can hope that it comes true. Can't I?"
"\n"
"\nI wasn't imagining things! Tonight in the hallway, Lord Maurice pulled me aside. He asked if I was married. If I had a family. Speechless would be a good word for my reaction. He's so—what's the word I'm looking for? Kind? Different? His father and mother beat me repeatedly for simple transgressions. But their son isn't like that. He's so nice. I'm still having a difficult time believing it. He wants to see me again. Alone. I'm not sure what to think about all this."
"\n"
"\nLord Maurice came to me again. He said he wanted to tell me something. He took my hand and led me off into the night. Hand in hand, we snuck through the gardens and sat on a bench beneath the moons. The way he looked at me sent shivers down my spine. "
"\n"
"\nOur love is forbidden. A rich noble like him and me, a simple servant. Still, we care for each other deeply. He plans to tell his parents of our love soon. I hope that goes well."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-760
msgctxt "51188213-0-760"
msgid "Claudie's Journal"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-728
msgctxt "21337012-0-728"
msgid "28th Sun's Dawn"
"\n"
"\nJa-Reet said he's leaving. Not leaving me, not exactly. Going to Black Marsh. He's never been there in his life. But, apparently, someone named Fal-Xoc there can help him."
"\n"
"\nAnd he told me, haltingly, how he thinks he's broken. I told him I love him the way he is. That it doesn't matter."
"\n"
"\nHe looked at me, and asked if it had ever hurt me. I had to nod."
"\n"
"\n""Then, yes,"" he said, ""it does matter."""
"\n"
"\nI cried. So did he. We went to bed without saying anything more."
"\n"
"\n19th Rain's Hand"
"\n"
"\nWe arrived in Percolating Mire today. There was a house ready for us. For Ja-Reet, really … there wasn't a bed for me. I was angry at Ja-Reet for leaving what we had together. It's taken us years to take my father's slave plantation and turn it into an ethical business. Years to get the community to accept a Dunmer-Argonian marriage."
"\n"
"\nHere, it's back to square one. A lizard-woman called me his ""friend."" Wouldn't use the word wife. I called her a name. I don't think she spoke the language, but she got the point."
"\n"
"\nLater:"
"\n"
"\nThe Dominion's landed in Shadowfen. I worry about the people here. Dunmeri villagers trained for invasion. Here … they're brave, but unarmed. We're in danger."
"\n"
"\nI asked Ja-Reet to leave, but he says he's making progress. I told him I think he's fine. He snapped at me that I don't get to decide whether he's fine or not."
msgstr ""

