msgctxt "21337012-0-1380"
msgid "First, the bear clawed at the tree. Then, he roared at it. He bit its bark and chewed. Yet the princess stayed safe, laughing all the while."
"\n"
"\nFinally, the bear sat back on its haunches and spoke. ""Why do you fear, little girl?"""
"\n"
"\nThe princess shouted down, ""Because you'll eat me, silly bear!"""
"\n"
"\nThe bear just shook its grizzled head. ""I do not eat children. Come down, and we will play a game."""
"\n"
"\nBut the princess was too clever for the crafty bear. She knew it was a trick. ""Come up here, if you're so eager for a game!"""
"\n"
"\nThe bear grunted. It began to climb."
"\n"
"\n<A handwritten note is scrawled in the margin of the page.>"
